    "body": "@holgerd77 \r\nAppreciate your feedback. You're correct, that a blog isn't the best place to document such a process. It is a better candidate for a Meta EIP (Process EIP) rather than a blog. \r\n\r\nThe process was proposed and [being iterated as a Meta EIP](https://github.com/poojaranjan/Ethereum-EIPs/blob/39181e8d376264d948963b33448a77fa38298164/EIPsForHardfork.md). \r\n\r\nWhile the decoupling of the EIP standardization & Network upgrade process was taking place, another decision was taken - **to keep everything related to the network upgrade out of the EIP GitHub repo**. It was then decided to add a part of the proposal to the [readme section of Eth1.0 spec](https://github.com/ethereum/eth1.0-specs#network-upgrade-process---eth10-specification) and details to be published in form of a blog. And thus the [Pull Request](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/pull/1929) documenting the process as a Meta EIP could never be merged. \r\n\r\nFrom a developers' point of view, I agree that having more information in GitHub would be helpful. I think it's a good suggestion to add more info to the Readme section.",
